events.title: Reception for 'Childish Work' Exhibition
events.description:
A closer look at "Childish Work," open now at GPS! üß∏üõùüé†

Don't forget to join us for the reception TONIGHT 6-8P! We hope to see you there! ü•Ç

************************

NOW OPEN @ GPS

Childish Work

Group Exhibition 

Curated by Inga Manticas

On View December 9-13, 2025

Reception: Friday, Dec 12th | 6-8p

Gallery Open Hours: 

Tuesday - Friday, 12-5p

Saturday, 2-5p

Some of the artists in the show make work out of found objects taken directly from their childhoods, like dollhouses and Fisher Price TVs. Others paint with their fingers or draw scenes on Shrinky Dinks. Others emulate the graphic styles of coloring books and comics. Others attempt to recreate distant childhood memories. Others make works that reference the forms of toys and dolls: objects that could hypothetically be played with, but also demand closer observation and may even repel touch.

events.title: Childish Work Group Exhibition
events.description:
The FINAL show of fall semester is here! Come by - this week only - to experience the childlike wonder that often accompanies this time of year üòâ üõùüé† Curated by current MFA in Art Candidate, Inga Manticas top10unexplainedcircles , the title of the show, Childish Work, turns an insult into an aspiration, or a genre. The show brings together fourteen artists between New York and North Carolina, each with a different connection to making childish work.
